# UI Components

## Main Layout Components

The application is divided into two main panels:

1. **Left Panel** ([src/index.html](mdc:src/index.html))
   - Image upload area
   - Extracted data display
   - Control buttons (Add Page, Save PDF)

2. **Right Panel** ([src/index.html](mdc:src/index.html))
   - Page display area
   - Legacy sheet template
   - Navigation controls

## Legacy Sheet Structure

Each legacy sheet has a specific structure:

1. **Generation Title** - Section header, e.g., "Sixth Generation"
2. **Person Entries** - Individual biographical entries with:
   - Person number
   - Person name and relationship text
   - Optional person image
   - Marriage details
   - Children list with markers (i, ii, iii, etc.)
3. **Dividers** - Horizontal rules separating entries
4. **Footer** - Contains report name and page number

## Navigation Controls

The UI includes several navigation and control elements:

- Pagination controls (Previous/Next buttons)
- Page indicator showing current/total pages
- Jump-to-page input
- Custom page numbering input
- Add/Delete page buttons
- Save state button
- Reset template button

## Guidelines For UI Modifications

1. Maintain the existing two-panel layout structure
2. Follow the legacy sheet format for content and styling
3. Keep navigation controls visually consistent
4. Preserve accessibility features
5. Ensure responsive behavior across different screen sizes
6. Test print functionality after UI changes
